<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FF37FAEEFEA20E4E" authority="Chambers &amp; Sparks &amp; Sydney &amp; Livingstone &amp; Cookson &amp; Whitworth, 2020" authorityName="Chambers &amp; Sparks &amp; Sydney &amp; Livingstone &amp; Cookson &amp; Whitworth" authorityYear="2020" box="[138,355,1327,1351]" class="Deltaproteobacteria" family="Myxococcaceae" genus="Myxococcus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Myxococcales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="eversor" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FF37FAEEFEA20E4E" box="[138,355,1327,1351]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">Myxococcus eversor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A249F97C6475D730FED7FAEEFE000E4E" box="[362,449,1327,1351]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314CB9E6475D730FF37FA9AFDA80E9B" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB198156475D730FF37FA9AFDA80E9B" blockId="11.[138,768,1371,1906]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FF37FA9AFE9D0E7B" authorityName="Chambers &amp; Sparks &amp; Sydney &amp; Livingstone &amp; Cookson &amp; Whitworth" authorityYear="2020" box="[138,348,1371,1394]" class="Deltaproteobacteria" family="Myxococcaceae" genus="Myxococcus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Myxococcales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="eversor">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FF37FA9AFE9D0E7B" box="[138,348,1371,1394]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">Myxococcus eversor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.ver’sor L. masc. n. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FDE4FA9AFD630E7B" authorityName="Chambers &amp; Sparks &amp; Sydney &amp; Livingstone &amp; Cookson &amp; Whitworth" authorityYear="2020" box="[601,674,1371,1394]" class="Deltaproteobacteria" family="Myxococcaceae" genus="Myxococcus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Myxococcales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="eversor">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FDE4FA9AFD630E7B" box="[601,674,1371,1394]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">eversor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the destroyer, reflecting its destruction of prey cells).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314CB9E6475D730FF15FA5AFC700A01" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB198156475D730FF15FA5AFD120C3B" blockId="11.[138,768,1371,1906]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">
Vegetative cells are Gram-negative bacilli tapering slightly at the ends, measuring 
<quantity id="4CF635F06475D730FEC3FA7AFE1E0EDB" box="[382,479,1466,1490]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.499999999999999" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" unit="m" value="0.6499999999999999" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.6">
0.6–0.7 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FE6FFA7BFE1E0EDB" bold="true" box="[466,479,1466,1490]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">m</emphasis>
</quantity>
m 3.0–8.0 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FDD5FA7BFDB40EDB" bold="true" box="[616,629,1466,1490]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">m</emphasis>
m in electron micrographs. Colonies exhibit swarming motility and appear pale brown on VY-2 agar (w/v 0.5% dried baker’s yeast, 0.1% CaCl 
<subScript id="178A9A506475D730FF40F9E4FEC60D3D" attach="left" box="[253,263,1573,1588]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">2</subScript>
2H 
<subScript id="178A9A506475D730FE91F9E4FEF70D3D" attach="right" box="[300,310,1573,1588]" fontSize="6" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">2</subScript>
O, and 1.5% agar). Fruiting bodies are irregular spheroids, orange in color. Aerobic growth was observed at 30–40 C, at pH 5.0–9.0, and with the addition of 1–4% NaCl. Hydrolyzes arginine, esculin, gelatin, 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FDFEF9BAFD910D9B" box="[579,592,1659,1682]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">p</emphasis>
-nitrophenyl- 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FD68F9BAFD220D9B" box="[725,739,1659,1682]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">B</emphasis>
-D-galactopyranoside, and urea. Assimilates 
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FDE4F95AFDA80DBB" box="[601,617,1691,1714]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">N</emphasis>
-acetyl-glucosamine, adipate, arabinose, caprate, citrate, gluconate, glucose, malate, maltose, mannitol, mannose, and phenyl acetate. Cells prey with low efficiency upon 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FDD4F93AFD250C1B" authority="TOP" authorityName="TOP" box="[617,740,1787,1810]" class="Gammaproteobacteria" family="Enterobacteriaceae" genus="Escherichia" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Enterobacteriales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Proteobacteria" rank="species" species="coli">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FDD4F93AFD680C1B" box="[617,681,1787,1810]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">E. coli</emphasis>
TOP
</taxonomicName>
10, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FF37F8DAFEA90C3B" authority="DSM" authorityName="DSM" box="[138,360,1819,1842]" class="Actinobacteria" family="Microbacteriaceae" genus="Clavibacter" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Actinomycetales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Actinobacteria" rank="species" species="nebraskensis">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FF37F8DAFEEF0C3B" box="[138,302,1819,1842]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">Cl. nebraskensis</emphasis>
DSM
</taxonomicName>
7483, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0EE3966475D730FE5FF8DAFD430C3B" authority="DSM" authorityName="DSM" box="[482,642,1819,1842]" class="Ustilaginomycetes" family="Ustilaginaceae" genus="Ustilago" kingdom="Chromista" order="Ustilaginales" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="maydis">
<emphasis id="B97A44076475D730FE5FF8DAFD860C3B" box="[482,583,1819,1842]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">U. maydis</emphasis>
<accessionNumber id="945D05F66475D730FDF2F8DAFD0D0C3B" box="[591,716,1819,1842]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/DSM14603" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">DSM 14603</accessionNumber>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB198156475D730FF15F8FAFAAC0A41" blockId="11.[138,768,1371,1906]" lastBlockId="11.[828,1461,235,328]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2300">
